(% style=&amp;#34;font-family:~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:inherit; mso-bidi-font-family:inherit;color:#636B75;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)1.(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34; ~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family: inherit; mso-bidi-font-family: inherit; color: rgb(99, 107, 117); mso-fareast-language: ZH-TW; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: ~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;&amp;#34; %)      (% style=&amp;#34;font-family:~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial; color:#636B75;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)We meet – we substantially increase incentives for production by the required percentage.
 DoD uses more energy than any other customer in the world.
 Michael J. Hornitschek ‘06, Lt Col, USAF ((% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34; ~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family: ~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 107, 117); mso-fareast-language: ZH-TW; border: none windowtext 1pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in&amp;#34; %)(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34; ~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family: ~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 107, 117); mso-fareast-language: ZH-TW; border: none windowtext 1pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; color: rgb(0, 137, 220); text-decoration: none; text-underline: none&amp;#34; %)http:~~/~~/www.au.af.mil/au/awc/awcgate/cst/csat56.pdf)url:http://www.au.af.mil/au/awc/awcgate/cst/csat56.pdf)

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt; margin-left:0in;line-height:16.8pt;background:white&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;color:#636B75; mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)Although the DoD uses only approximately 1.5 percent of the 20    million barrels of oil consumed each day in the U.S., it is the largest single    institutional energy customer in the United States and likely the world. 5
 2. Counter-interpretation – substantially means materially or essentially.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt; margin-left:0in;line-height:16.8pt;background:white&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;color:#636B75; mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)Words and Phrases ’02 (Words and Phrases Permanent Edition, “Substantial,” Volume 40A, p. 448-486 October 2002, Thomson West)

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt; margin-left:0in;line-height:16.8pt;background:white&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;color:#636B75; mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)M.D.Tenn. 1941. Word “substantial” means in substance or in a substantial manner, materially, or essentially. – Newark Stove Co. v. Gray and Dudley Co., 39 F.Supp. 992.
 3. Additionally, substantially must be evaluated within the context of the plan.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt; margin-left:0in;line-height:16.8pt;background:white&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;color:#636B75; mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)Words and Phrases ’02 (Words and Phrases Permanent Edition, “Substantial,” Volume 40A, p. 448-486 October 2002, Thomson West)

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;margin-top:6.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:6.0pt; margin-left:0in;line-height:16.8pt;background:white&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;color:#636B75; mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)Cust and Pat.Ap. 1946. The word “substantially” in claim of application for patent for a mine ventilator for a motor and switch in a substantially complete enclosure did not mean the same word as “essentially”, but was a relative term to be interpreted in accordance with context.
 4. Their interpretation is arbitrary – neg teams can just find a definition for any percentage that happens to exclude the aff.
 5. We preserve predictability – all topic literature is about whether certain changes will be made to incentives, not about how much of a percentage increase will ensue.
 6. They kill aff ground – reforming existing policies is not topical under their interpretation because that requires a qualitative, legal change.
 7. Percentage tests are arbitrary, and courts have abandoned them because they obscure complex issues in favor of numbers.

(% class=&amp;#34;MsoNormal&amp;#34; style=&amp;#34;line-height:16.8pt;background:white&amp;#34; %)
(% style=&amp;#34;font-family:~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;; color:#636B75;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)Kindell and Reilly, &amp;#39;97
 (EO CPE Lobbyist, (% style=&amp;#34;font-family:~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial; color:#636B75;border:none windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-alt:none windowtext 0in; padding:0in;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)(% style=&amp;#34;font-family: ~&amp;#34;inherit~&amp;#34; ~&amp;#34;serif~&amp;#34;; mso-fareast-font-family: ~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial; color: rgb(99, 107, 117); border: none windowtext 1pt; mso-border-alt: none windowtext 0in; padding: 0in; mso-fareast-language: ZH-TW; color: rgb(0, 137, 220); text-decoration: none; text-underline: none&amp;#34; %)ftp:~~/~~/66.77.65.232/pub/irs-tege/eotopicp97.pdf)url:ftp://66.77.65.232/pub/irs-tege/eotopicp97.pdf)(% style=&amp;#34;font-family:~&amp;#34;Arial~&amp;#34;,~&amp;#34;sans-serif~&amp;#34;;mso-fareast-font-family:~&amp;#34;Times New Roman~&amp;#34;; color:#636B75;mso-fareast-language:ZH-TW&amp;#34; %)
 Most cases have either tended to avoid any attempt at percentage measurement of activities or
 AND
 complexity of balancing the organization’s activities in relation to its objectives and circumstances.” 
